### invoice-service - przykłady requestów
###
### Plik dla IntelliJ HTTP Client
### Konfigurację wartości zmiennych ustaw w pliku `http-client.env.json`
### obok tego pliku, np.:
###
### {
###   "local": {
###     "API_URL": "http://localhost:8082",
###     "WEBHOOK_TOKEN": "secret",
###     "WEBHOOK_APP_NAME": "fakturownia"
###   }
### }

### 1. Health check
GET {{API_URL}}/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

### 2. POST /invoices - happy path (DRAFT -> ISSUED)
POST {{API_URL}}/invoices
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{$uuid}}",
  "taxId": "1234567890",
  "buyerName": "Test Buyer Sp. z o.o.",
  "items": [
    { "name": "Product A", "quantity": 1, "price": 99.99, "taxRate": 23 },
    { "name": "Product B", "quantity": 2, "price": 10.50, "taxRate": 8 }
  ]
}

> {%
client.global.set("invoiceId", response.body.invoiceId);
%}

### 3. GET /invoices/{id}/pdf - cold cache (z Fakturowni)
GET {{API_URL}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/pdf
Accept: application/pdf

### 4. GET /invoices/{id}/pdf - warm cache (z bazy)
GET {{API_URL}}/invoices/{{invoiceId}}/pdf
Accept: application/pdf

### 5. POST /invoices - validation error (puste items)
POST {{API_URL}}/invoices
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{$uuid}}",
  "taxId": "1234567890",
  "buyerName": "Test",
  "items": []
}

### 6. POST /invoices - validation error (ujemna cena)
POST {{API_URL}}/invoices
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{$uuid}}",
  "taxId": "1234567890",
  "buyerName": "Test",
  "items": [
    { "name": "Bad", "quantity": 1, "price": -5, "taxRate": 23 }
  ]
}

### 7. POST /invoices - duplikat order_id (oczekiwane: idempotent recovery)
# Powtórz request 2 razy z tym samym orderId. Drugi powinien wrócić
# istniejącą fakturę (status ISSUED) zamiast rzucać 409.
@duplicateOrderId = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111

POST {{API_URL}}/invoices
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{duplicateOrderId}}",
  "taxId": "1234567890",
  "buyerName": "Idempotent Test",
  "items": [{ "name": "X", "quantity": 1, "price": 10, "taxRate": 23 }]
}

### 8. Webhook - poprawny token (oczekiwane: 200/404)
POST {{API_URL}}/webhooks/fakturownia/invoices/update
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 999001,
  "deal": { "external_ids": { "invoice_id": 999001 } },
  "app_name": "{{WEBHOOK_APP_NAME}}",
  "api_token": "{{WEBHOOK_TOKEN}}"
}

### 9. Webhook - zły token (oczekiwane: 401)
POST {{API_URL}}/webhooks/fakturownia/invoices/update
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 999002,
  "deal": { "external_ids": { "invoice_id": 999002 } },
  "app_name": "{{WEBHOOK_APP_NAME}}",
  "api_token": "wrong-token"
}

### 10. Webhook - nieznany app_name (oczekiwane: 401)
POST {{API_URL}}/webhooks/fakturownia/invoices/update
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 999003,
  "deal": { "external_ids": { "invoice_id": 999003 } },
  "app_name": "unknown-client",
  "api_token": "{{WEBHOOK_TOKEN}}"
}

### 11. Webhook - brak external_id w deal (oczekiwane: 200, no-op)
POST {{API_URL}}/webhooks/fakturownia/invoices/update
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 999004,
  "deal": { "external_ids": {} },
  "app_name": "{{WEBHOOK_APP_NAME}}",
  "api_token": "{{WEBHOOK_TOKEN}}"
}

### 12. GET /invoices/{id}/pdf - nieistniejące id (oczekiwane: 404)
GET {{API_URL}}/invoices/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/pdf
Accept: application/pdf
